The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for the correction of phase errors in diffusion-weighted MRI images. This involves image processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm also involves the use of a convolutional neural network, which is a popular deep learning technique used in computer vision and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the reduction of computational complexity, which is a common topic in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE) research. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a sub-topic of multimedia (cs.MM) research.
